The President signed the James Zadroga 9/11 Health and Compensation Act to provide medical monitoring and treatment for those affected by the World Trade Center disaster. This includes rescue workers, residents, students, and others suffering from health consequences. The President acknowledged the bravery of firefighters, police officers, and first responders who risked their lives to save others. He stated that this act is a critical step for those who still bear the physical scars of the attacks.